<subSubSection id="A19CF2C7FFC4FFD4FF37FE42FBC674A3" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E939A14CFFC4FFD4FF37FE42FBDF743C" blockId="15.[151,1436,329,678]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FF37FE42FEB777AC" bold="true" box="[199,315,401,426]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the first record of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="2E86DACFFFC4FFD4FCFFFE42FC2677AC" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[783,938,401,426]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FCFFFE42FC2677AC" box="[783,938,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Brachypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="9191E1DCFFC4FFD4FC0DFE41FBA177AF" box="[1021,1069,402,425]" name="Iran" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="2E86DACFFFC4FFD4FB3FFE41FAB277AC" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[1231,1342,401,426]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valgus">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FB3FFE41FB6C77AF" box="[1231,1248,402,425]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FB05FE42FAB277AC" box="[1269,1342,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">valgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from those of other 
<taxonomicName id="2E86DACFFFC4FFD4FDC8FE66FD5877C8" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[568,724,437,462]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FDC8FE66FD5877C8" box="[568,724,437,462]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Brachypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following combination of characters: frons predominantly shiny black, with narrow greyish pollinose vitta along eye margin; face predominantly black with a pair of lateral yellowish-orange vittae; scutum with yellowish pile; legs partly yellow; tergite 5 with brownishblack pile and a longitudinal depression on each side of posterolateral third of tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E939A14CFFC4FFD4FF37FD95FBC674A3" blockId="15.[151,1436,329,678]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">
In the Middle East, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="2E86DACFFFC4FFD4FDE5FD96FD3C7458" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1834" box="[533,688,581,606]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FDE5FD96FD3C7458" box="[533,688,581,606]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Brachypalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded first from the Asian part of 
<collectingCountry id="9191E1DCFFC4FFD4FB76FD96FB5B7458" box="[1158,1239,581,606]" name="Turkey" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="2E86DACFFFC4FFD4FAF0FD96FE1F7484" authority="Schiner, 1857" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meigeni">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FAF0FD96FF7C7487" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">Brachypalpus meigeni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8D17DCBDFFC4FFD4FF07FDBAFE1F7484" author="Schiner" box="[247,403,617,642]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" refString="Schiner, I. R. (1857) Diptera Austriaca. Aufzahlung aller im Kaiserthume Oestereich bisher aufgefundenen Zweiflugler. III. Die ostereichischen Syrphiden. Uerhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft, Wien, 7, 279 - 506." type="journal article" year="1857">Schiner, 1857</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="2E86DACFFFC4FFD4FD8DFDB9FD6A7484" baseAuthorityName="Panzer" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[637,742,617,642]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Brachypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valgus">
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FD8DFDB9FD027487" box="[637,654,618,641]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="DBF27D5EFFC4FFD4FD6DFDBAFD6A7484" box="[669,742,617,642]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="42">valgus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="8D17DCBDFFC4FFD4FD0FFDBAFCF77484" author="Peck" box="[767,891,617,642]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" refString="Peck, L. V. (1988) Syrphidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Akademia Kiado, Budapest, pp. 11 - 230." type="book chapter" year="1988">Peck 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D17DCBDFFC4FFD4FC77FDBAFB177484" author="Vujic" box="[903,1179,617,642]" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" refString="Vujic, A. &amp; Milankov, V. (1999) New data for the tribes Milesiini and Xylotini (Diptera, Syrphidae) on the Balkan Peninsula. Dipteron, 2 (6), 113 - 132." type="journal article" year="1999">Vujić &amp; Milankov 1999</bibRefCitation>
). The female collected in the present study represents the second record of this genus from the Middle East.
</paragraph>
